The paper deals with capacity pre-log of a communication channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The channel is a SIMO (single-input multiple-output) channel, which is a common topic in signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of algebraic geometry (cs.CC) and Hironaka's Theorem (cs.SY) in the proof of their main result.
